This product includes software developed by the following projects:

---

Lean 4
Copyright 2021-2024 Lean FRO, LLC
License: Apache-2.0
https://github.com/leanprover/lean4

Ferriprove is designed to be compatible with Lean 4's kernel language
and type theory. The reference implementation defines the target semantics
that Ferriprove aims to match.

---

nanoda_lib
Copyright 2021-2024 ammkrn
License: MIT
https://github.com/ammkrn/nanoda_lib

Ferriprove's design and implementation references nanoda_lib as prior art
for Rust-based Lean kernel checking. The project serves as an audit baseline
for Ferriprove's kernel implementation.

---

Lean4Lean
Copyright 2021-2024 digama0
License: Apache-2.0
https://github.com/digama0/lean4lean

Ferriprove uses Lean4Lean as the proof oracle for formal verification
of the pure kernel via Aeneas translation. Lean4Lean provides the
metatheory that Ferriprove's soundness proofs are checked against.

---

lean-kernel-arena
Copyright 2021-2024 Lean FRO, LLC
License: Apache-2.0
https://github.com/leanprover/lean-kernel-arena

Ferriprove participates in the kernel arena as an external checker.
The arena provides the test corpus that Ferriprove validates against.

---

Aeneas
Copyright 2021-2024 AeneasVerif
License: Apache-2.0
https://github.com/AeneasVerif/aeneas

Ferriprove uses Aeneas to translate its pure Rust kernel to Lean for
formal verification. This enables soundness proofs to be checked against
Lean4Lean's metatheory.

---

